Package qlang.core.lang

Class Visitor

java.lang.Object
org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
qlang.core.interpreter.QBaseVisitor<Value>
qlang.core.lang.Visitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<Value>, QVisitor<Value>
public class Visitor extends QBaseVisitor<Value> implements Cloneable
All of these methods follow a simple format, essentially the following: visit_____Expression(params) The _____ is always replaced with what the method does Typically, they are self-explanatory, for instance 'visitSelfExpression' is what handles the 'self' keyword The most important class by far: the visitor class. This class visits each of the nodes generated by lexing and parsing the given file or project in Q. These javadoc comments were automatically generated, so they aren't the best. Feel free to add context to them. I'll likely work more on these comments later, its just a huge endeavour, since it has so many methods which all have different purposes.
